<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="384" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[1280,2130,1158,1427]" pageId="67" pageNumber="384">
The term 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simpson" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1513,1739,1160,1196]" class="Mammalia" family="Pediomyinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="67" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Pediomyinae</taxonomicName>
was used first in the discussion of the Hell Creek fauna by 
<bibRefCitation author="SIMPSON, G. G." journalOrPublisher="Amer. Mus. Novitates" pageId="67" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 7" part="267" refId="ref63475" refString="SIMPSON, G. G. 1927 a. Mammalian fauna of the Hell Creek Formation of Montana. Amer. Mus. Novitates, no. 267, pp. 1 - 7, figs. 1 - 6." title="Mammalian fauna of the Hell Creek Formation of Montana" type="journal article" year="1927">Simpson (1927a)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="CLEMENS, W. A." box="[1442,1712,1252,1287]" journalOrPublisher="Univ. California Publ. Geol. Sci." pageId="67" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 122" part="62" refId="ref56477" refString="1966. Fossil mammals of the type Lance Formation, Wyoming. Pt. 2. Marsupialia. Univ. California Publ. Geol. Sci., vol. 62, pp. 1 - 122, figs. 1 - 77, tables 1 - 24." title="Fossil mammals of the type Lance Formation, Wyoming. Pt. 2. Marsupialia" type="journal article" year="1966">Clemens (1966)</bibRefCitation>
raised the subfamily to familial status by proposing the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simpson" authorityYear="1927" class="Mammalia" family="Pediomyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="67" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Pediomyidae</taxonomicName>
, but restricted it to include only a single genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marsh" authorityYear="1889" box="[1402,1549,1390,1425]" class="Mammalia" family="Peradectidae" genus="Pediomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="67" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1402,1549,1390,1425]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="384">Pediomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
